definitions.definition: A built-in function that is implemented directly by the compiler , without any intermediate call to a library .
An ability possessed by a character and not requiring any external equipment .
examples: You can acquire the fire-resistance intrinsic by eating dragon meat.

main_definition: ( computing , programming ) A built-in function that is implemented directly by the compiler , without any intermediate call to a library .
